The paper presents a method for using standard techniques from satisfiability checking to automatically verify and discover theorems in an area of economic theory known as ranking sets of objects. This involves formulating candidates for impossibility theorems in propositional logic and searching for them using a SAT solver. This approach involves elements of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic (cs.LO), game theory (cs.GT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
